<p>According to documentation <a href="http://cxf.apache.org/distributed-osgi-reference.html" rel="nofollow">http://cxf.apache.org/distributed-osgi-reference.html</a>:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>CXF/DOSGi allows you to add the distribution properties to existing   OSGi services. You can do this by installing a bundle that contains an   XML file with the extra properties in the OSGI-INF/remote-service   directory:</p> </blockquote>  <p>but I couldn't manage to get it to work with dosgi-cxf 1.7.0 in Karaf 4.</p>  <p>I installed dosgi-cxf in karaf:</p>  <pre><code>feature:repo-add mvn:org.apache.cxf.dosgi/cxf-dosgi/1.7.0/xml/features feature:install cxf-dosgi-discovery-local </code></pre>  <p>I created scr component using bndtools that is published to osgi-registry.</p>  <pre><code>@Component(immediate = true, provide = OfficeResource.class) public class OfficeResourceImpl implements OfficeResource {  ... } </code></pre>  <p><a href="https://github.com/antoniomaria/karaf4-eclipselink-jpa/blob/master/rest-ds/src/main/java/net/sf/companymanager/rest/impl/OfficeResourceImpl.java" rel="nofollow">See all code</a>.</p>  <p>The bundle decorator contains a /OSGI/remote-service/sd.xml:     /OSGI-INF/remote-service/alt-remote-services.xml --></p>  <pre><code>    &lt;match interface="net.sf.companymanager.rest.OfficeResource"&gt;       &lt;add-property name="service.exported.interfaces" value="*" /&gt;       &lt;add-property name="service.exported.configs" value="org.apache.cxf.rs" /&gt;       &lt;add-property name="org.apache.cxf.rs.httpservice.context" value="/api" /&gt;       &lt;add-property name="org.apache.cxf.rs.address" value="/" /&gt;       &lt;add-property name="service.exported.intents" value="HTTP" /&gt;     &lt;/match&gt;   &lt;/service-decoration&gt; &lt;/service-decorations&gt; </code></pre>  <p><a href="https://github.com/antoniomaria/karaf4-eclipselink-jpa/blob/master/rest-ds-discovery/src/main/resources/OSGI-INF/remote-service/sd.xml" rel="nofollow">See all code</a>.</p>  <p>I am expecting that <a href="https://github.com/apache/cxf-dosgi/blob/master/dsw/cxf-dsw/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/dosgi/dsw/decorator/ServiceDecoratorBundleListener.java" rel="nofollow">ServiceDecoratorBundleListener</a> add those properties to my OfficeResource service. But finally cxf properties are not injected:</p>  <pre><code>karaf@root()&gt; service:list net.sf.companymanager.rest.OfficeResource [net.sf.companymanager.rest.OfficeResource] -------------------------------------------  component.id = 1  component.name = net.sf.companymanager.rest.impl.OfficeResourceImpl  service.bundleid = 56  service.id = 186  service.scope = bundle Provided by :  cm :: Module  :: Rest Service ( Declarative Services) (56) </code></pre>  <p>I also checked the bundle start level:</p>  <pre><code>cxf-dosgi-ri-dsw-cxf &lt; my_bundle_which_has_sd.xml &lt; my_bundle_which_has_myexistingservice </code></pre>  <p>Do I misss something, or that feature is broken hence the documentation says:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>@@@ TODO check that this still works with the 1.2 release.</p> </blockquote>